defaul:
  image: python:3.10-bookworm

stages:
  - ci_setup
  - build
  - test
  - lint
  - format
  - deploy

variables:
  POETRY_VIRTUALENVS_IN_PROJECT: true
  # PIP_REQUIRE_VIRTUALENV: true
  POETRY_CACHE_DIR: ${{ github.workspace }}/poetry-cache

cache:
  key: \${CI_COMMIT_REF_SLUG}"
  paths:
    - .venv
    - .cache/pip
    - /usr/local/bin/

ci_setup:
  stage: ci_setup
  script:
    - python3 -m pip install poetry==1.7.1
    - poetry config http-basic.gitlab $CI_JOB_TOKEN "x-access-token"
    - which poetry

build:
  stage: build
  dependencies:
    - ci_setup
  script:
    - make dist
  artifacts:
    paths:
      - ./dist
    expire_in: 1 hour

test:
  stage: test
  dependencies:
    - ci_setup
  script:
    - make test

lint:
  stage: lint
  dependencies:
    - ci_setup
  script:
    - make lint

format:
  stage: format
  dependencies:
    - ci_setup
  script:
    - make format

deploy:
  stage: deploy
  dependencies:
    - ci_setup
  script:
    - poetry publish -r gitlab
  only:
    - _ci_dev
    - release
"

id: bad-actor-ruleset
title: \Bad Actor Ruleset"
tags:
  - integration
  - guardrails
  - policy
  - ruleset
---

<!-- WARNING This file is maintained in the whylabs-ai/whylogs-container-python repository. Don't manually edit without also updating that. -->

<head>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://docs.whylabs.ai/docs/secure/bad-actor-ruleset/" />
</head>

Bad Actor is designed to prevent bad actors from interacting with your LLM applications through the detection of jailbreak and injection attacks.

The following yaml code can be added to your policy to enable the Bad Actor ruleset.

```yaml
  - ruleset: score.bad_actors
    options:
      behavior: observe
      sensitivity: medium
```

This ruleset adds the equivelant of the following metric section to your yaml policy and uses those metrics to compute an overall score.

```yaml
metrics:
  - metric: prompt.similarity.jailbreak
  - metric: prompt.similarity.injection
```"

  publish-docs-to-gitlab:
    name: Update docs.whylab.ai
    needs: publish-python-client
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout
        uses: actions/checkout@v3

      - name: Configure Git
        run: |
          git config --global user.email \ci@whylabs.ai"
          git config --global user.name "GitHub Actions for whylabs-ai/whylogs-container-python"

      - name: Push File to GitLab
        env:
          GITLAB_ACCESS_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITLAB_DOCUMENTATION_REPO }}
        run: |

# whylogs-container-client

A client library for accessing FastAPI

## Usage

First, create a client:

```python
from whylogs_container_client import Client

client = Client(base_url=\https://api.example.com")
```

If the endpoints you're going to hit require authentication
column3:

```

Now call your endpoint and use your models:

```python
from whylogs_container_client.models import MyDataModel
from whylogs_container_client.api.my_tag import get_my_data_model
from whylogs_container_client.types import Response

with client as client:
    my_data: MyDataModel = get_my_data_model.sync(client=client)
    # or if you need more info (e.g. status_code)
    response: Response[MyDataModel] = get_my_data_model.sync_detailed(client=client)
```

Or do the same thing with an async version:

```python
from whylogs_container_client.models import MyDataModel
from whylogs_container_client.api.my_tag import get_my_data_model
from whylogs_container_client.types import Response

async with client as client:
    my_data: MyDataModel = await get_my_data_model.asyncio(client=client)
    response: Response[MyDataModel] = await get_my_data_model.asyncio_detailed(client=client)
```

with
  giftcard_sale as (
    select
      dtl.business_day_date,
      dtl.ringing_store_num,
      sum(
        CASE
          WHEN dtl.line_net_usd_amt=100 THEN 1
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) no_100,
      sum(
        CASE
          WHEN dtl.line_net_usd_amt=200 THEN 1
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) no_200,
      sum(
        CASE
          WHEN dtl.line_net_usd_amt=250 THEN 1
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) no_250,
      sum(
        CASE
          WHEN dtl.line_net_usd_amt=500 THEN 1
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) no_500,
      sum(
        CASE
          WHEN dtl.line_net_usd_amt=1000 THEN 1
          ELSE 0
        END
      ) no_1000
    from
      prd_nap_usr_vws.RETAIL_TRAN_DETAIL_FACT_VW dtl
    where
      dtl.business_day_date BETWEEN '2023-10-01' AND '2023-10-07'
      and dtl.nonmerch_fee_code='6666'
      and dtl.tran_type_code='SALE'
      and dtl.data_source_code='POS'
      and dtl.line_net_usd_amt in (100, 200, 250, 500, 1000)
    group by
      1,
      2
  )
select
  cal.day_date business_day_date,
  TO_CHAR (cal.store_num) as ringing_store_num,
  coalesce(gc.no_100, 0) no_100,
  coalesce(gc.no_200, 0) no_200,
  coalesce(gc.no_250, 0) no_250,
  coalesce(gc.no_500, 0) no_500,
  coalesce(gc.no_1000, 0) no_1000
from
  (
    select
      day_date,
      store_num
    from
      prd_nap_usr_vws.day_cal
      full outer join prd_nap_usr_vws.JWN_STORE_DIM_VW on 1=1
    where
      day_date BETWEEN '2023-10-01' AND '2023-10-07'
  ) cal
  left join giftcard_sale gc on cal.day_date=gc.business_day_date
  and cal.store_num=gc.ringing_store_num;
